Summary “A digital marketer’s first responsibility is to understand what is happening so they can improve upon it. Underneath that mandate lie hundreds of detailed questions about customers, platforms, channels and technologies. Answering them depends on collecting accurate, timely data using a variety of website tags. “ - Econsultancy & Tealium, The ROI of Tag Management, 2012 

In my roles as Global Product Owner - Dynamic Remarketing and EMEA Product Lead - Remarketing & Conversion Tracking, my day was focused primarily on Google tags. Through this role I learned that not everyone shares the same passion for tagging that I do!! 

An engineer by trade, I am designed to seek out problems and solve them. To help solve our clients' tagging problems, we created the Implementation team in November 2013. A small scrappy team of 3 covering EMEA, our aim was simple: "Install The Tags." Remarketing, Conversion Tracking, Google Analytics and Google Tag Manager (GTM) were my tools and I was the craftsman. Working with some of Google's largest clients, I created complete tagging solutions and executed them within a quick 1-2 week Time-To-Live turn around time. 

I soon learned that there were many more tags in the tagging universe; AdRoll, Criteo, CoreMetrics, Marin, Turn to name only a few. As a tagging specialist I often engaged in pitch meetings offering my expertise as to why one solution was more effective than the other. Complete industry knowledge was essential for these engagements. 

I am an expert in Remarketing / Retargeting, Conversion Tracking, Google Analytics, Google Tag Manager, developing & delivering trainings. I simply do love tagging. I also love knitting, traveling, technology, drinking tea and meeting new people! If you would like to chat about any of these things please do reach out! Introduction to Google Tag Manager Edit Summary “A digital marketer’s first responsibility is to understand what is happening so they can improve upon it. Underneath that mandate lie hundreds of detailed questions about customers, platforms, channels and technologies. Answering them depends on collecting accurate, timely data using a variety of website tags. “ - Econsultancy & Tealium, The ROI of Tag Management, 2012 

