As the SalesTech Global Product Support Owner for Dynamic Remarketing, it was my responsibility to ensure complete global 2nd level support of the AdWords Dynamic Remarketing Product suite. It was this role that earned me my first promotion at Google, and later led to my position on the then newly formed Implementation team. 

Key Skills and Responsibilities 

● Co-leading a team of 10 support members globally, known as the Remarketing Pod; 

● A deep understanding of the product, both from a technical and usage side; 

● Prioritizing high level escalations from top AdWords customers; 

● Communicating effectively with engineering and other technical groups to enhance products and resolve customer issues; 

● Maintaining an effective feedback loop between the support team, the Remarketing pod, the product and engineering teams, in addition to handling feedback from AdWords customers and the Sales teams; 

● Developing and distributing documentation and training on support solutions, both internally and externally. AdWords Technical Specialist, SalesTech Google September 2011  –  November 2013  (2 years 3 months) EMEA HQ, Dublin, Ireland The SalesTech team is a 2nd level solution-generating force that helps Google's sales teams and advertisers. These solutions need to be scalable to support thousands of AdWords customers worldwide. 

Key Skills and Responsibilities 

● Advanced knowledge of the entire AdWords Product Suite; 

● Quickly identifying and addressing customer concerns in real-time (< 1 hr). Working to resolve at least 50% of issues within real time (<1 hr). The remaining issues (with the exception of bugs) to be resolved within 5 hours; 

● Analysing support data to identify trends and communicate actionable insights to product stakeholders and sales; 

● Projects included: 

○ Ownership of the global AdWords Known Issues Page; 

○ Involvement in the development of the Internal Help Centre, growing it from an online folder of resources that my team referenced, to a fully integrated and accessible help centre. 


In addition to core work, I specialised in analysing support data to identify trends and communicate actionable insights to product stakeholders and the sales teams. Primarily, these reports allowed me to identify product areas where the Sales teams were in need of additional training.  
